title: Concussion rate in the U.S. 2010 to 2015 , by age
summary: Overall Rate per 1,000 members has decreased over the Year.
Rate per 1,000 members is slightly decreasing from 18-19_years to 25-29_years, and finally roughly constant from 25-29_years to 35-39_years.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 18-19_years and 20-24_years.
Maximum Rate per 1,000 members, about 10.1 was reported at Year 18-19_years
Minimum Rate per 1,000 members about 2.0 was reached at Year 30-34_years, and 35-39_years
